+# AGENTS.md
+
+## Project Identity
+
+This repository implements Pala Memory Core, a local-first AI work memory system for capturing, summarizing, linking, reporting, and backing up ChatGPT/Codex work.
+
+## Working Rules
+
+- Preserve the local-first design.
+- Prefer Markdown + JSON + SQLite over opaque storage.
+- Keep records human-readable.
+- Never publish secrets, API keys, local tokens, private credentials, or sensitive user data.
+- Treat backup as evidence storage, not release approval.
+- Keep changes small, reversible, and tied to the requested workflow.
+- Prefer reliable manual commands before browser/mobile automation.
+
+## Core Commands
+
+| Command | Meaning |
+|---|---|
+| `pala remember` | Save active work into a memory record |
+| `pala brief today` | Summarize today's records |
+| `pala link project` | Attach a record to a repo/folder |
+| `pala report` | Produce a Markdown report |
+| `pala backup github` | Publish report package to knowledge bank |
+
+## Required Record Fields
+
+Every saved memory record should include:
+
+- `id`
+- `created_at`
+- `source`
+- `title`
+- `summary`
+- `raw_text_path`
+- `attachments`
+- `project_refs`
+- `tags`
+- `decisions`
+- `tasks`
+- `evidence`
+- `backup_status`
+
+## Knowledge Bank Integration
+
+For meaningful Pala OS reports or implementation mutations, prepare a report package for:
+
+```text
+trugurpala/pala-os-bilgi-bankasi
+```
+
+Required package:
+
+- Implementation Report
+- Changed Files Manifest
+- Repo Change Review
+- Raw Patch/Diff, when practical
+
+## Completion Output
+
+At the end of a task, report:
+
+- What changed
+- Which files were added or changed
+- Which commands were used as evidence
+- Backup status
+- Remaining risk
+- Next best step
+
