+# Install
+
+Pala Memory Core MVP is a local-first Python starter. It does not require a database, cloud account, or paid service for the first version.
+
+## Requirements
+
+| Requirement | Version |
+|---|---|
+| Python | 3.10+ |
+| OS | Windows, macOS, Linux |
+| Optional | Git |
+
+## Quick Start
+
+From the repository root:
+
+```powershell
+python pala.py remember --title "First memory" --text "Pala Memory Core is installed." --source manual --tag setup
+python pala.py brief today
+python pala.py backup receipt
+python pala.py dashboard export
+python pala.py dashboard serve
+```
+
+Generated files appear under:
+
+```text
+data/
+  records/
+  reports/
+  attachments/
+  backups/
+```
+
+## Open The Dashboard
+
+The MVP dashboard can be served locally:
+
+```powershell
+python pala.py dashboard serve
+```
+
+Then open:
+
+```text
+http://127.0.0.1:8765
+```
+
+The dashboard can also be opened as static HTML:
+
+```text
+dashboard/index.html
+```
+
+Open it in a browser. Later versions can read live records from the local data folder.
+
+## Daily Use
+
+| User Intent | Command |
+|---|---|
+| Save a useful ChatGPT/Codex answer | `python pala.py remember --title "..." --text "..." --source codex` |
+| Save text from a file | `python pala.py remember --title "..." --text-file note.txt` |
+| Attach a PDF or screenshot | `python pala.py remember --title "..." --file doc.pdf --file screen.png` |
+| Connect to a repo | `python pala.py remember --title "..." --project trugurpala/pala-os-v4` |
+| Make today's summary | `python pala.py brief today` |
+| Create local backup receipt | `python pala.py backup receipt` |
+| Update dashboard data | `python pala.py dashboard export` |
+| Open local dashboard | `python pala.py dashboard serve` |
+
+## First Public Repo Setup
+
+Recommended repository name:
+
+```text
+trugurpala/pala-memory-core
+```
+
+Recommended first files:
+
+```text
+README.md
+AGENTS.md
+INSTALL.md
+pala.py
+schema/record.schema.json
+docs/commands.md
+docs/connectors.md
+docs/roadmap.md
+docs/security.md
+dashboard/index.html
+examples/sample-record.json
+```
