+# Security And Privacy
+
+Pala Memory Core is designed to store personal AI work. That can include private chats, code, PDFs, screenshots, business notes, and credentials accidentally pasted into a conversation.
+
+## Default Policy
+
+| Rule | Meaning |
+|---|---|
+| Local-first | Keep records on the user's machine unless backup is requested |
+| Explicit backup | Do not upload automatically in MVP |
+| Human-readable | Store Markdown so the owner can inspect records |
+| No secrets | Redact API keys, tokens, passwords, cookies, and private credentials |
+| Backup receipt | Record where files were backed up |
+| Recovery by evidence | Store enough metadata to find work later |
+
+## Sensitive Data To Filter
+
+- API keys
+- OAuth tokens
+- Session cookies
+- SSH keys
+- `.env` files
+- Database dumps
+- Customer data
+- Private documents
+- Local runtime secrets
+
+## Backup Targets
+
+| Target | Use | Caution |
+|---|---|---|
+| Local folder | Primary storage | Needs disk backup strategy |
+| GitHub | Public report/evidence links | Do not publish secrets or private data |
+| Google Drive | Private file backup | OAuth and sharing permissions matter |
+| Obsidian/Logseq vault | Personal reading/search | Sync settings may upload files |
+
+## Release Rule
+
+Backup is not release approval. A record can be backed up and still be marked as partial, blocked, or needs review.
+
