+# v0.1 Acceptance Criteria
+
+## Goal
+
+Pala Memory Core v0.1 proves the core loop:
+
+```text
+capture -> local record -> daily brief -> local backup receipt
+```
+
+The version is complete when a user can save useful ChatGPT/Codex work locally, generate a daily summary, and produce a backup receipt without needing cloud services.
+
+## Required User Flows
+
+| Flow | Command | Completion Evidence |
+|---|---|---|
+| Save a text memory | `python pala.py remember --title "..." --text "..."` | Markdown and JSON record created under `data/records/` |
+| Save with project link | `python pala.py remember --title "..." --text "..." --project trugurpala/repo` | JSON contains `project_refs` |
+| Save with attachment | `python pala.py remember --title "..." --file file.pdf` | File copied under `data/attachments/` and hash stored |
+| Create daily brief | `python pala.py brief today` | Markdown brief created under `data/reports/` |
+| Create backup receipt | `python pala.py backup receipt` | Receipt created under `data/backups/` |
+| Export dashboard data | `python pala.py dashboard export` | `dashboard/records.json` created |
+| Serve dashboard locally | `python pala.py dashboard serve` | Local HTTP server exposes dashboard files |
+
+## Required Files
+
+| File | Purpose |
+|---|---|
+| `README.md` | Explain the product and MVP |
+| `INSTALL.md` | Explain local install and first commands |
+| `AGENTS.md` | Explain agent working rules |
+| `pala.py` | MVP CLI |
+| `schema/record.schema.json` | Record contract |
+| `docs/commands.md` | Command reference |
+| `docs/connectors.md` | Connector model |
+| `docs/security.md` | Privacy and backup rules |
+| `dashboard/index.html` | Static dashboard preview |
+| `examples/sample-record.json` | Example record |
+
+## Non-Goals
+
+- No automatic ChatGPT history scraping
+- No mobile background capture
+- No Google Drive upload yet
+- No GitHub write API yet
+- No vector search yet
+- No secret scanner guarantee yet
+
+## Definition Of Done
+
+| Check | Expected Result |
+|---|---|
+| CLI capture | Creates valid record files |
+| Attachment copy | Does not mutate original file |
+| Brief generation | Includes today's records and open tasks |
+| Backup receipt | Shows local complete, GitHub/Drive pending |
+| Dashboard preview | Opens as static HTML |
+| Dashboard data export | Static dashboard can read `records.json` |
+| Dashboard local server | Dashboard can be served at `http://127.0.0.1:8765` |
+| Docs | New user can understand first three commands |
+
+## Release Posture
+
+`v0.1` is a local prototype. It is usable for personal capture experiments, but not ready for automatic private data backup or public multi-user use.
